# Handwritten Digit Recognition

This repository contains a simple Python script for handwritten digit recognition using scikit-learn's SVM classifier. The script trains a Support Vector Machine on the digits dataset and predicts the values of handwritten digits.

## Usage

### Prerequisites

- [Conda](https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/latest/user-guide/install/index.html) must be installed on your system.

### Setup

1. **Clone the repository:**

    git clone https://github.com/mohamedatawfik/learning-analytics.git

2. **Navigate to the project directory:**

    cd learning-analytics/scikit_machine_learing_tool

3. **Create and activate the Conda environment:**

    conda env create -f environment.yml
    conda activate digit-classification

4. **Running the Script:**

    python handwritten-digit-recognition.py

